tags.name: King's Drive
tags.note: Reported to have been planted with Sycamore trees to create a direct route from Plessey Station to North Drive for Edward VII Prince of Wales in the late 1890's.
Bing imagery is dated 2012 so has this area been clearfelled and changed use?
trees are quite young, only a few years old in 2020, so not really a 'wood' just yet
